==English==
===Adjective===
'''quintic'''

#{{mathematics}} Of or relating to the [[fifth]] [[degree]], such as a quintic [[polynomial]] which has the form  ax<sup>5</sup>+bx<sup>4</sup>+cx<sup>3</sup>+dx<sup>2</sup>+ex+f (containing a term with the independant variable raised to the fifth power).


===Noun===
'''quintic''' 

#{{mathematics}} a quintic [[polynomial]]: ax<sup>5</sup>+bx<sup>4</sup>+cx<sup>3</sup>+dx<sup>2</sup>+ex+f


